In [20]:
depts = db.departmennt.unique() 
gb = db.groupby('departmennt')    
rets = []
sats = []
times = []
sals = []

for dept in depts:
    df = gb.get_group(dept)
    ret = ((df['left'] == 0).sum()/df['left'].count())
    rets.append(ret)
    sat_mean = df['satisfaction_level'].mean()
    sats.append(sat_mean)
    time_mean = df['time_spend_company'].mean()
    times.append(time_mean)
    sal_mean = df['salary'].mean()
    sals.append(sal_mean)

plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12,8)
my_colors = 'c'  #red, green, blue, black, etc.

bar = plt.bar(depts, rets, color=my_colors)
plt.ylabel('Employee Retention Rate', fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel('Department', fontsize=15)
plt.show()
In [21]:
def subcategorybar(X, vals, width=0.8):
    n = len(vals)
    _X = np.arange(len(X))
    #for i in range(n):
    plt.bar(_X - width/2. + 0/float(n)*width, vals[0], 
                width=width/float(n), align="edge", label='Satisfaction Level')
    plt.bar(_X - width/2. + 1/float(n)*width, vals[1], 
                width=width/float(n), align="edge", label='Time Spent')
    plt.bar(_X - width/2. + 2/float(n)*width, vals[2], 
                width=width/float(n), align="edge", label='Salary')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(_X, X)

plt.figure(figsize=(14,8))
plt.title('Department vise Average Attributes', fontsize=15)
subcategorybar(depts, [sats,times,sals])

plt.show()
In [22]:
sals = db.salary.unique() 
gb = db.groupby('salary')    
tots = []
working = []


for sal in sals:
    df = gb.get_group(sal)
    working.append((df['left'] == 0).sum())
    tots.append(df['left'].count())

def subcategorybar(X, vals, width=0.8):
    n = len(vals)
    _X = np.arange(len(X))
    #for i in range(n):
    plt.bar(_X - width/2. + 0/float(n)*width, vals[0], 
                width=width/float(n), align="edge", label='Total Employeees', color = 'steelblue')
    plt.bar(_X - width/2. + 1/float(n)*width, vals[1], 
                width=width/float(n), align="edge", label='Employees Still Working', color = 'lightsteelblue')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(_X, X)

plt.figure(figsize=(14,8))
sals_label = ['Low', 'Medium', 'High']
subcategorybar(sals_label, [tots, working])
plt.ylabel('Number of Employes', fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel('Salary Group', fontsize=15)

plt.show()

In [25]:
distortions = []

for i in range(2,16):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i)
    kmeans.fit(N)
    distortions.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,8))
plt.plot(range(2,16), distortions)
plt.grid(True)
plt.title('Elbow Curve', fontsize=20)
plt.show()

In [32]:
left = db['left']
labels = labels.astype(np.float)

tp = ((left==1) & (labels==1)).sum()
tn = ((left==0) & (labels==0)).sum()
fp = ((left==0) & (labels==1)).sum()
fn = ((left==1) & (labels==0)).sum()

confusion_matrix = np.array([tp,fp,fn,tn]).reshape(2,2)
g = sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix, annot=True, fmt = ".0f", cmap = "coolwarm", xticklabels=['Cluster 1', 'Cluster 2'], yticklabels=['Left', 'Working'])
g.figure.set_size_inches(5, 4);
